
**  Checking ansible version result:

 $ ansible --version


** Running ls command on specifique host ( icamaragcloud )

$ ansible -i hosts.ini  icamaragcloud -m command -a "ls /"


ansible -i hosts.ini  icamaragcloud -m ping

** The ansible play-book command

$ ansible-playbook playbook.yml -i hosts.ini

 ** ssh command when you have more than one ssh key

  ssh -i ~/.ssh/gcloud-ssh-key.pub icamaraus@35.190.211.3


** Login in mysql server and getting default users


$ sudo mysql -u root # I had to use "sudo" since is new installation

mysql> USE mysql;
mysql> SELECT User, Host, plugin FROM mysql.user;



